-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-03/u-k-stocks-climb-benchmark-ftse-100-snaps-four-day-drop.html
U.K. stocks advanced, snapping a
four-day retreat for the benchmark FTSE 100 Index, as basic-
materials and utility companies rose.  The FTSE 100 increased 24.56 points, or 0.4 percent, to
5,736.04 at 8:24 a.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
